main event: On June 6, 1955, multiple sightings of unidentified objects occurred in Parker, Arizona, involving ground radar and visual observations.
interesting points: Three objects observed on ground radar for 15 minutes moving northeast and then east,The objects were described as yellow, white, and red,The objects appeared to travel at high speeds,The report includes an observation of a circular, brightly lighted object approximately 25-30 feet in diameter,Investigation conducted by military personnel revealed no conclusive evidence.
sighted object: Three unidentified objects on radar and a circular, brightly lighted object in the sky
witness description: The sightings involved various witnesses including Mr. Wallace A. Watts and Mr. John Doe, who were accompanied by family members.
